<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-01-29T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-01-29T12:00:00-05:00" n="384" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d384">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 BE/1–2954 Telegram</note>
                            <head>No. 384<lb/><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <gloss target="#t_niact1"><hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi></gloss></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-01-29T18:00:00+01:00">January 29, 1954—6
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 17. Eyes only for Acting
                                Secretary. We start immediately preparing position and tactics with
                                British and French for restricted meeting of four Ministers next
                                week. I intend to submit tomorrow to working group now set up by
                                three Western delegations substance of proposal contained in <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 10<note n="1" xml:id="d384fn1"><ref target="#d369">Document 369</ref>.</note> and approved
                                by <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 5.<note n="2" xml:id="d384fn2">See <ref target="#d369fn3">footnote 3, <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi></ref>.</note> I would hope this
                                could then become basis for agreed position of <persName corresp="#p_BGP1">Bidault</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_EASA1">Eden</persName> and myself.</p>
                            <p>I would appreciate, therefore, any necessary preparations in
                                Washington being started at once, including, I would think,
                                notifying confidentially <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>,
                                    <persName>Arthur Dean</persName><note n="3" xml:id="d384fn3">U.S. Special Ambassador for the Korean Political
                                    Conference.</note> and American Embassy Seoul in view
                                possibility leaks from British or French. Of course we cannot be
                                sure British–French concurrence so project must be regarded highly
                                tentative.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_DJF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>